peopleAlsoAsk.question: How to authenticate a vintage Mickey Mouse watch?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: 1) Licensed MM watches from the 30's through the 60's will have an Ingersoll trademark on them. Later watches will have a Disney trademark label on them. If you can't find a trademark its a fake. 2) From 1933 to 1946 Ingersoll was the ONLY licensed manufacturer of MM watches.
